cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about a new benchmark dataset for natural language understanding (NLU) and the performance of models trained on this dataset. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also discusses the shortcomings of current state-of-the-art models and the use of non-expert annotators, which suggests that it could also fit into the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of image-based NLI, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the iterative, adversarial human-and-model-in-the-loop procedure used to collect the dataset could also make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
